@ryanofsky @promag Thank you for your reviews.

Updated 44f7f519e5fc7aef6df12474ce3c9b8583e6f20b -> 24a90d54ed31fd3da787b95e29e2fca581235836 ([pr18897.02](https://github.com/hebasto/bitcoin/commits/pr18897.02) -> [pr18897.03](https://github.com/hebasto/bitcoin/commits/pr18897.03), [diff](https://github.com/hebasto/bitcoin/compare/pr18897.02..pr18897.03)).

Ready for review now :)

@fanquake 
> @hebasto can you either move this over to the GUI repo, or close and we'll mark it up for grabs? The interested re-opener can open it in the gui repo.

https://github.com/bitcoin-core/gui/pull/260

No reason to tie this to to the CHECK_NONFATAL implementation or to have exceptions pass through QT code which by design does not use them. Would change this to not be tied to a specific exception type:

```
try {
    bumpFeeHelper();
} catch (const std::exception& e) {
    Q_EMIT runawayException(QString::fromStdString(e.what()));
} catch (...) {
    Q_EMIT runawayException("Unkno

Why emit a signal? No one is interested in this signal right? Could just call another slot in a generic catcher, like:
```cpp
template <typename F> void shieldException(F&& f) {
    try {
        f();
    } catch (...) {
        QMetaObject::invokeMethod(qApp, "messageException", Qt::QueuedConnection,
            Q_ARG(QString, exception_message), ...
        );
    }
}
